<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10018e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10018e">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10018e"> 18(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> brick thrown / blindfold reveals / site ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>LIBRARY 4,000 YEAR&apos;S OLD. PROFESSOR&apos;S STORY OF DIVINATION.</b> &ldquo;In despair, and grasping a chance of divination, I went alone to the top of the mound and chose a <mark>brick</mark> of the age of Nebuchadnezzar, which lay at my feet, and marked on it an arrow. Then, <mark>after blind-folding myself</mark> and turning round many times to lose my bearings, <mark>I threw backwards</mark> over my head. The next morning digging was recommenced <mark>at the place indicated</mark> by the arrow, and within two hours a large nest of valuable literary tablets was found.&rdquo; <small> <a name="IT1apr24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#IT1apr24"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (1 April 1924) 5/5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01004f" href="c01all.htm#c01004f">VI.C.01:004(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
